last_episode_to_air.name: Bark If You See 'Em
last_episode_to_air.overview: The final four teams rev up in Edmonton for a showdown; they face twists and turns and a chance to make a giant leap towards the finish line.

name: The Amazing Race Canada
overview: A uniquely Canadian take on the original series, with ten teams of two racing around the world to amazing locations for the $1,000,000 prize.

episodes.name: Where In the World is Ogopogo?
episodes.overview: Nine teams from across the country arrived at the starting line in Niagara Falls, Ont., by high speed jet boats ready to run “The Amazing Race Canada.”

episodes.name: Se Hou Leng
episodes.overview: The remaining eight teams race through Vancouver's urban jungle.

episodes.name: Hoodoos and Hoodonts
episodes.overview: In Calgary, one team steers the others in a different direction; they line up, get knocked down, and face a dirty detour.

episodes.name: Grab a Nug
episodes.overview: As the contestants travel by land and water across northern Canada, a Speed Bump affects one team in the Yukon.

episodes.name: Death by Lentils
episodes.overview: The racers head to Regina, Sask., where they are buried in lentils and questioned by the RCMP

episodes.name: Check the Cannons!
episodes.overview: The remaining teams get tongue-tied and crushed by crepes in Quebec City while the sisters make a costly decision.

episodes.name: We Don't Have Time for the Bathroom
episodes.overview: The teams head to the frozen climate of Iqaluit, Nunavut; Celina has trouble eating a local delicacy; and the contestants embark on a climb.

episodes.name: Clutch and Release
episodes.overview: The four remaining teams race into Nova Scotia, where Vanessa and Celina encounter problems, Dave loses patience with Jet and things get intense at the race's second U-Turn.

episodes.name: Ah-mazing
episodes.overview: The Top 4 teams race to Newfoundland and Labrador.

episodes.name: The Family Race Off
episodes.overview: The Top 3 teams go to Toronto for the final leg of the race.

episodes.name: What's It Take to Get a Cup of Tea?
episodes.overview: Eleven new teams begin a race for an unprecedented grand prize.

episodes.name: There's a Fish in My Pants
episodes.overview: The remaining teams race to Tofino, British Columbia; things turn a little fishy at the detour.

episodes.name: Snakes and Liars
episodes.overview: The remaining teams are pushed like never before when they travel to Hong Kong, China.

episodes.name: They're Harshing Our Mellow
episodes.overview: The remaining teams race to Macau, China and face a confusing casino challenge.

episodes.name: Who Designs These Torture Tests?
episodes.overview: After flying to the Yukon, an Express Pass giveaway causes trouble and one team is sent packing.

episodes.name: She's the Pierogi Poobah
episodes.overview: The “Race” continues in Winnipeg where teams struggle with scoring goals and channel their inner rock stars at a karaoke challenge.

episodes.name: Lest We Forget
episodes.overview: The teams horse around in Normandy and take a moment to honour fallen soldiers.

episodes.name: I Said Yes!
episodes.overview: In romantic Paris, the teams are brought to a standstill at the roadblock

episodes.name: How Are We Going to Explain This to Mom and Dad?
episodes.overview: The race goes into high gear in Montreal; the teams get confused by a cheesy Detour; the contestants bare it all.

episodes.name: Hot Poop
episodes.overview: Teams go back in time in Charlottetown; the teams end up in a dead heat.

episodes.name: Put the Fun Back in Fundy
episodes.overview: The teams face a complex detour as they race to New Brunswick, fighting to be one of the 3 teams in the final leg.

episodes.name: Who's Da Bomb?
episodes.overview: The final three teams are pushed to their limits in Ottawa and the winning team takes the gold.

episodes.name: Who's Feeling Sporty Now
episodes.overview: The 12 teams begin their epic journey in front of the Chateau Frontenac in Québec City, then travel to Toronto.

episodes.name: We're Going to Dance!
episodes.overview: Teams are surprised with an early adventure outside of Canada when they travel to South America. In Santiago, Chile, tensions run high and racers fly higher. Some teams struggle to communicate with the locals, while others express themselves with body language, as they race for a pair of Express passes.

episodes.name: I Said Straight, You Gorilla
episodes.overview: Teams race to Buenos Aires, Argentina, where racers begin at the Plaza Canada Totem Pole, before getting tripped up on the field in a game of blind soccer.

episodes.name: We Know Where They Live
episodes.overview: Teams head home to Halifax, where a lost passport puts one team in jeopardy of losing it all.

episodes.name: The Face Off
episodes.overview: Teams discover one of Québec’s hidden gems, the Magdalen Islands, where they fight to stay afloat in the series’ first ever Face Off challenge.

episodes.name: Who Is Alex Trebek?
episodes.overview: Teams continue to race to Sudbury, Ontario, where the drama continues, and the trauma gets critical. The Detour forces teams to take the plunge and go deep underground.

episodes.name: I Dream About Eating Sandwiches
episodes.overview: The Road Block in Saskatoon has some teams bouncing ahead while others fall behind.

episodes.name: All of These Are the Same
episodes.overview: The remaining teams travel to Kolkata, India, and face chaos in the streets.

episodes.name: Take Your Clue and Goooo!
episodes.overview: Things get slippery and spicy in Delhi, India for the remaining teams.

episodes.name: Man I've Got a Big Butt
episodes.overview: A Road Block leaves some of the teams ramped up in Okanagan Valley, British Columbia.

episodes.name: Cabotage
episodes.overview: The final four teams race to Edmonton where they step back in time and Face Off on the ice.

episodes.name: Here's to You, Canada... Cheers
episodes.overview: The final three teams race to Vancouver and Whistler and face with the most terrifying challenge ever. The first one to cross the finish line will be crowned the season-three champions.

episodes.name: Who's Ready to Let It All Hang Out?
episodes.overview: Ten teams begin the adventure of a lifetime in the rugged frontier of The Northwest Territories.

episodes.name: Deal Guys? Deal! Deal!
episodes.overview: The remaining teams race to downtown Calgary; a detour leaves some of the racers' heads spinning.

episodes.name: Toads! Are You Kidding Me?
episodes.overview: The remaining teams race to Mekong where they must contend with the heat and culture.

episodes.name: Shine Your Light
episodes.overview: The teams race through the streets of Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam

episodes.name: The Little Blind Tugboat That Could
episodes.overview: After returning home to British Columbia, the remaining teams experience Haida Gwaii.

episodes.name: Am I Actually Operating the Plane?
episodes.overview: The teams fly to Hamilton, Ontario where they receive messages from home.

episodes.name: I Could Be Prime Minister
episodes.overview: Tensions build as the teams race toward Kingston, Ont.

episodes.name: I Just Wanna Win
episodes.overview: The remaining teams hit the streets of Havana, Cuba.

episodes.name: For Those About to Rock
episodes.overview: The teams return to Canada and race through Nova Scotia where a Detour has some teams up in arms.

episodes.name: We're Doing It Wrong! We're in Big Trouble
episodes.overview: The remaining teams race to Saint John, N.B. where a Detour puts them in a sticky situation.

episodes.name: Second Place Isn't Good Enough
episodes.overview: The final three teams fly to Montreal and are tested mentally, physically, and emotionally for the final leg.

episodes.name: Who Wants to Be the Python?
episodes.overview: Ten teams kick off the race at Signal Hill National Historic Site and travel to Vancouver.

episodes.name: You've Got to Leave My Hose Alone Dude!
episodes.overview: The teams race to Fort McMurray, Alta., where some start to feel the pressure with three express passes up for grabs.

episodes.name: It's Like Ducks in the Forest
episodes.overview: The teams race to Castlegar, B.C., where grueling challenges lead some teams to spiral out of control with three Express Passes in play.

episodes.name: This Is a Butt Workout
episodes.overview: In Beijing, some Racers find themselves lost in translation on the Great Wall of China, while others consider throwing in the towel.

episodes.name: This Is a Real Cat and Mouse Chase
episodes.overview: The Race continues through Shanghai, China, and Bangkok, Thailand, where a Detour has Racers struggling to hang loose.

episodes.name: We Just Saw Johnny Mustard
episodes.overview: The teams head to Ottawa, where a citizenship test has some Racers struggling to make the grade and it's a fight for first to the Double U-Turn.

episodes.name: Break Time for Korey
episodes.overview: The Race heads back to Newfoundland and Labrador, where alliances crumble, tensions boil, and the teams are faced with the first face-off of the season.

episodes.name: Can I See Your Kuna?
episodes.overview: The teams head south to Panama City where a Detour has some teams letting loose, and a Roadblock has Racers feeling colour blind.

episodes.name: It's Like Finding Waldo in a Bunch of Waldos
episodes.overview: The teams face a detour in Regina; the odds are stacked against some teams.

episodes.name: They're Crawling on You
episodes.overview: The remaining teams travel to Sault Ste. Marie, where some struggle to jump through hoops, and the final four face their fears.

episodes.name: Canada's Coming Together Like a Piece of Cake
episodes.overview: The final three teams race to the finish line.

episodes.name: After the Race
episodes.overview: Viewers now have a chance to re-live all the memorable moments and watch an exclusive first chat with the finalists and newly crowned winners with “After the Race,” a one-hour after-show special immediately following the final episode.Shot live and hosted for a second time by “The Social’s” Melissa Grelo, Cynthia Loyst, Lainey Lui, and Marci Ien, the fan-favourite special will reunite all 10 teams to dish on all the details and the drama during their time on the “Race.”

episodes.name: Just a Beaver Hero
episodes.overview: The “Heroes edition” of the Race begins with 10 teams of Canadian heroes at Hatley Castle in Colwood, Victoria.

episodes.name: Fiddler's Fart
episodes.overview: The remaining teams head North to Dawson City, Yukon where 3 Express Passes are up for grabs.

episodes.name: Sounds Like a Wild Boar
episodes.overview: The teams head to Salt Spring Island, B.C., where they face a speedy Roadblock.

episodes.name: Just Suck My Blood Please
episodes.overview: The teams head to Jakarta, Indonesia where they face a blind Double U-Turn.

episodes.name: You Gotta Whip That Cream
episodes.overview: The teams return to Canada to duel in Stratford, Ontario.

episodes.name: Smells Like Sweat and Fun
episodes.overview: The teams keep racing and join the masses in Toronto, where a roadblock has teams trying to get ahead of the pack.

episodes.name: Poodle Time
episodes.overview: The remaining teams travel to Winnipeg, where they attempt to hit the bullseye in a Face Off.

episodes.name: The Zombies Are Honing in on Us
episodes.overview: The remaining teams head east to Prince Edward Island.

episodes.name: The Battle of the Two Courtneys
episodes.overview: The remaining teams head to Mexico City, where they act out.

episodes.name: The Plan Is Simple. Win!
episodes.overview: The remaining 4 teams return to Canada to compete for a spot in the finale.

episodes.name: The Summer of Heroes
episodes.overview: The three remaining teams race to the finish line in the hope of claiming victory.

episodes.name: Canada Get More Maps
episodes.overview: The Amazing Race Canada returns for Season 7 as nine new teams join Canada’s Choice Jet and Dave at the starting line in Toronto.

episodes.name: Our Competition's Not That Smart
episodes.overview: Teams race to Revelstoke, B.C., where some wipe out and others find themselves halted on the track to the pit stop.

episodes.name: We'll Let the Peasants Fight for Last Place
episodes.overview: In Edmonton, some teams get blindsided by the first-ever One Way.

episodes.name: I Love Geologists
episodes.overview: The teams travel to Yellowknife, where racers feel the pressure of a diamond road block before things take a chilling turn

episodes.name: Clamageddon Continues
episodes.overview: Teams head southwest to Nanaimo, B.C., where they take their fears to new heights and are challenged during a search on the beach.

episodes.name: I'm a Little Muskrat on a Mission
episodes.overview: The race leads to Saskatoon, where some teams find themselves stuck and others dance around the problem.

episodes.name: Balls, Balls, Balls
episodes.overview: Teams head to Kitchener-Waterloo, Ont., where the season’s first face-off forces racers to prove that they’re best in class

episodes.name: Open Your Bouche
episodes.overview: Teams travel to Charlevoix, Que., where some racers get tongue-tied under pressure.

episodes.name: Another Day in Thunder Bay
episodes.overview: Racers head to Thunder Bay, Ont., where a Face Off makes teams realize it could be anybody’s game.

episodes.name: He's Basically a Hound
episodes.overview: The final four teams head east to Wolfville, Nova Scotia, and the Annapolis Valley, where they compete for a spot in the Season 7 finale.

episodes.name: I Had ONE Job
episodes.overview: The final three teams race to the finish line in Muskoka, Ont. in hopes of winning Season 7 of The Amazing Race Canada.

episodes.name: Come On, Doodlebug
episodes.overview: On the season premiere, 10 new teams embark on an epic adventure that could change their lives forever.

episodes.name: Goatageddon
episodes.overview: Teams race to Lethbridge, Alta., where some decide to give a hoot, while others follow the herd.

episodes.name: We Love Weenies!
episodes.overview: Racers make their way to Fernie, B.C., where they must choose between learning to fly or ready to roll.

episodes.name: Feel the Fear and Do It Anyways
episodes.overview: Teams head to Canmore, Alberta, where they must race the rapids before hitting the ranch for a test of skill and stamina.

episodes.name: I'm a Human Kite
episodes.overview: Teams jet off to Kelowna, B.C., where they take their fears to great heights and set their sights on a new target.

episodes.name: Racing for Our Lives
episodes.overview: Racers head to London, Ont. where they choose between aviation or animation, before they are joined by some furry friends.

episodes.name: What the Duck Is Going On?
episodes.overview: Teams make their way to Prince Edward County, Ont. where a shocking surprise sends the racers reeling.

episodes.name: Give Me a Moustache and Call Me Sherlock Holmes
episodes.overview: Teams travel to Ottawa and Gatineau, Que., where the season’s first Face Off quickly reveals that this is still anybody’s game.

episodes.name: I Love You. I Know.
episodes.overview: Racers jet off to Bathurst, N.B., where they put their footwork to the test; some realize they might not be doing as ‘well’ as they thought.

episodes.name: Is That a Wild Peacock?
episodes.overview: The remaining teams head to Tobermory, Ont. and the Bruce Peninsula, where they compete for a spot in the finale.

episodes.name: Where Is Gurmail
episodes.overview: On the season finale, the final teams are pushed to the limit to earn the coveted title of THE AMAZING RACE CANADA champions.

episodes.name: I Hate Pancakes
episodes.overview: An epic race throughout Canada begins, as 10 teams embark on the adventure of a lifetime. Starting in Winnipeg, before heading to Calgary, racers face their first challenges as they compete to be first at the mat.

episodes.name: My First Experience
episodes.overview: Racers wade into Smithers, B.C., where some have a smooth delivery and others struggle with the details.

episodes.name: Bribery Always Works
episodes.overview: Racers head to Whistler and Pemberton, B.C., where some take a leap and others take a plunge.

episodes.name: This Ugly Duckling Is Now a Swan
episodes.overview: In Victoria, B.C., teams strive for precision during the first Face Off and try to avoid making a splash while balancing in the ocean.

episodes.name: This Is Not a Hot Girl Moment
episodes.overview: Teams travel to Tofino and Ucluelet, B.C., where things get icy before they take a dive.

episodes.name: This Is Going to Be a Spicy Leg
episodes.overview: The race heads east to Niagara-on-the-Lake, Ont., where a roadblock has teams revved up and they try to sniff out a win.

episodes.name: I'm Sick of Wearing Neon
episodes.overview: Teams slip and slide in Windsor Ont., and must hold’em or fold’em in a high stakes Face Off.

episodes.name: I Should Have Made Snowmen
episodes.overview: Teams travel to Saguenay, QC, where things get rocky as racers hang on for a spot in the semi-finals.

episodes.name: Light the Candle
episodes.overview: The teams make their way to Toronto, where after the opening bell, racers are faced with a tough climb.

episodes.name: Do You Want Some Candies
episodes.overview: The Race continues in Toronto, where the remaining teams compete for a coveted spot in the Season 9 finale.

episodes.name: It's Zebra Time
episodes.overview: The last remaining teams face an intense final race to the finish line, as they defy gravity to hit a target and square off.

episodes.name: Back Where It All Started
episodes.overview: The milestone tenth season returns to where it all began, as 11 teams embark on the adventure of a lifetime.

episodes.name: Call Me the Olive Man
episodes.overview: Teams head west to the Sunshine Coast, B.C., and decide whether to secure their spot or try for an opportunity to get ahead.

episodes.name: Plot Twist It's a U-Turn Vote
episodes.overview: Faced with the first-ever U-Turn Vote, alliances are formed and threatened as some teams realize they're being played.

episodes.name: Slow Roll and Stay in Control
episodes.overview: In Penticton, B.C., the drama from the U-Turn Vote unfolds when the results are revealed, and another twist leaves everyone shocked.

episodes.name: I Smell Like Carcass
episodes.overview: Teams head to Regina, Sask. before 'The Amazing Race Canada' touches down in host Jon Montgomery’s hometown of Russell, Man.

episodes.name: Caution Double Pass Ahead
episodes.overview: The Race heads east to Guelph and Wellington County, Ont., where teams first take a moment to reflect before getting boosted 90 feet up a limestone quarry.

episodes.name: When Am I Going to See My Dog Next?
episodes.overview: Tensions are high during a Face Off as teams sweep into a Switch Back in Trois-Rivieres, Que. The detour leaves some tongue tied, while others get into a paper jam. At the roadblock teams struggle to hold their horses.

episodes.name: Manure Time Baby!
episodes.overview: The Race continues in Cornwall, Ontario and reaches a fever pitch before alpaca poop hits the fan and a Detour leaves racers off-kilt; it's game on as teams bank on scoring a spot in the semi-final.

episodes.name: Where Are You Mr. Oyster
episodes.overview: Racers make waves on the East Coast and try to zip through the competition in Miramichi, New Brunswick; the heat is on as the remaining teams try to earn their way into a coveted spot on the season ten finale.

episodes.name: Bark If You See 'Em
episodes.overview: The final four teams rev up in Edmonton for a showdown; they face twists and turns and a chance to make a giant leap towards the finish line.
